@startuml
title NILM Pipeline - Single Laptop Deployment

node "User Laptop" <<device>> {

  artifact "Web Browser\n(Dashboard UI)" as browser

  node "Local Application Environment" <<execution environment>> {
    
    artifact "Backend API Service" as backend
    artifact "Data Reader Module" as reader
    artifact "NILM Model Service\n(or integrated module)" as model_service
    artifact "Trained NILM Model\n(.pkl / .h5)" as model_file
    
    database "Meter Data SQL DB\n(pre-seeded data)" as meter_db
    database "Historical SQL DB\n(results + logs)" as sql_db
  }
}

' Relationships
browser --> backend : HTTP (localhost)
backend --> reader
reader --> meter_db : SQL query (local)
backend --> model_service : internal call
model_service --> model_file
backend --> sql_db : SQL insert/select (local)

@enduml


' For development and demonstration purposes, the entire NILM pipeline is deployed on a single laptop. All services (backend API, NILM model service, and databases) run locally. Although everything is hosted on one device, the architecture preserves modular separation so that individual components can later be migrated to separate servers or cloud environments without redesigning the system.